FBIS4-66021 "drweu103_q_94007" FBIS-WEU-94-103 Daily Report 26 May 1994 TURKEY Two Injured in Grenade Explosion in Istanbul Two Injured in Grenade Explosion in Istanbul TA2605181894 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1700 GMT 26 May 94 TA2605181894 Ankara TRT Television Network Turkish BFN [Announcer-read report over video] [Text] Terrorists threw concussion grenades at the fast tramway station in Aksaray, Istanbul. Two persons were injured in the incident. Two terrorists placed a concussion grenade at the main entrance gate of the fast tramway station around 1745. Two as yet unidentified persons were slightly injured in the explosion. The explosion also caused slight damage at the station. A bomb placed in a garbage can in front of a fast-food counter in Aksaray also exploded around the same time. No one was killed or injured in the explosion. Security forces are continuing their search operations to apprehend the terrorists.
